============================================================

The improvement plan is written to `tools/title-loop/docs/10-d73df28/improvement-plan.md`.

**Key findings and proposed fixes:**

1. **Feedback correction**: The feedback's root cause for Failure 1 is wrong — "CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM" has 5 words (not 6), so the pre-filter doesn't penalize it. The actual root cause is that `bestStructural` may resolve to "WARZYWA I BOCZEK" instead of the real title, causing the prefix filter to target the wrong heading, letting "CHLEBEK" (a sub-section header) survive to kill the real title via dedup.

2. **Fix 1 — Polish metadata patterns**: Add `NA\s+\d`, `DLA\s+\d`, `\d+\s*MIN`, `\d+\s*GODZ` patterns to `looksLikeMetadata`. Directly fixes Failure 2 ("NA 3 PAPRYKI") and also catches OCR-corrupted time metadata like "PRZYGOTOWANTE 20 MIN" and "GOTOMANTE 15 MIN".

3. **Fix 2 — Pre-dedup sub-section header removal**: Before the "shorter wins" dedup, remove ALL_CAPS candidates that are (a) followed by ingredient lines AND (b) are substrings of another surviving candidate. Directly fixes Failure 1 by removing "CHLEBEK" before it can kill the real title.

4. **Fix 3 — Structural heading tiebreaker** (defense-in-depth): When two structural headings have nearly equal rawScores (within 0.03), prefer the longer/earlier one. Makes the prefix filter more reliable.
