{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UvcEb9Ss8NfNqSXXHwGaZ1","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary of Title Extraction Iterations 1–9\n\nI've read all feedback and improvement plan documents. Here's a concise synthesis organized by iteration:\n\n---\n\n### **Iteration 1 (Baseline Failure Analysis)**\n**Failures identified:** 5 cases failed, 1 passed\n- **ARAYES SHRAK:** Short split titles lost to substring fragments\n- **Baked Eggs:** Metadata lines (SERVES) incorrectly joined with title\n- **Finnish Flatbreads:** OCR corruption fragments ranked higher than real titles\n- **Pizza Dough:** Embedding failed to rank technique-oriented titles correctly\n- **Saffron Wheat Buns:** Deep-document titles buried by early garbled text\n\n**Key patterns identified:**\n1. No recipe metadata filtering\n2. No OCR quality validation\n3. Embedding scoring unreliable for distinguishing titles from body text\n4. Position underweighted as signal\n5. Multi-line title joining fragile (no distinction between complete title and noise)\n6. `+`-join output format ambiguous (conflates multi-part titles with spurious matches)\n\n---\n\n### **Iteration 2 (Strategy: Bonuses)**\n**Plan:** Add position bonus, metadata blocklist, OCR quality gate, ALL_CAPS bonus, stricter thresholds\n**Problems:** Not fully implemented\n\n---\n\n### **Iteration 3 (Strategy: Invert Dedup, Reduce Position, Structural Heading)**\n**Key changes:**\n- Inverted substring dedup (longer candidate wins on ties)\n- Reduced position bonus from additive to multiplicative (tiebreaker only)\n- Added \"first structural ALL_CAPS heading\" bonus (+0.10)\n- Strengthened garble detection\n\n**Result:** Still failing — dedup logic backward\n\n---\n\n### **Iteration 4 (Diagnosis: Dedup + Threshold Leakage)**\n**Identified:** \n- Dedup \"shorter wins\" destroys correct multi-line joins (partial title beats full join)\n- Position boost inflates threshold, excluding late-document titles\n- Continuation logic depends on selecting correct base heading\n\n**Plan:** Use final score in dedup, make baseHeading embedding-aware, reduce threshold leakage\n**Problem:** Changes not implemented in code\n\n---\n\n### **Iteration 5 (Partial Implementation)**\n**Attempted:** Origin tracking, continuation join protection\n**Failures:** 3 cases still failing\n- Dedup still kills continuation joins (suffix fragments survive, kill complete join)\n- Structural bonus inflates threshold, excluding second recipe titles\n- OCR fragments hijack structural heading role\n\n---\n\n### **Iteration 6 (Embedding-Quality BaseHeading Selection)**\n**Key changes:**\n- Track candidate `origin` (single/2-line/3-line)\n- Protect continuation joins from dedup\n- Exclude structural bonus from threshold computation\n- Select baseHeading by embedding quality, not position\n- OCR truncation cross-validation penalty\n\n**Failures:** 2 cases failing\n- Continuation suffix still kills join (protection only one-directional)\n- OCR character mismatch (`:` vs `/`) breaks evaluation\n\n---\n\n### **Iteration 7 (Suffix Fragment + Separator Normalization)**\n**Key changes:**\n- Remove BOTH prefix and suffix continuation fragments before dedup\n- Normalize `/` ↔ `:` in evaluation harness\n- Hard disqualification for truncated headings (rawScore = -1.0)\n\n**Result:** Still failing on new test cases\n\n---\n\n### **Iteration 8 (Structural Signals Before Embedding)**\n**Key insight:** Structural signals (ALL_CAPS, continuation chars, position) are MORE reliable than embeddings. Treat them as pipeline shapers, not bonuses.\n\n**Changes:**\n- Pre-merge continuation lines (lines starting with `/&+:(`)\n- Ingredient-gap detection in multi-title guard (distinguish recipe sections from separate recipes)\n- First-line mixed-case protection (promote position-0 titles over position-1 ALL_CAPS subtitles)\n\n**New failures:** 2 cases\n- Mixed-case title with ingredient names scored below threshold (embedding penalizes ingredient words)\n- Bilingual recipe: first-line protection ineffective when ALL_CAPS inflates threshold beyond mixed-case title's reach\n\n---\n\n### **Iteration 9 (Threshold Fallback + Pre-Threshold Bilingual Detection)**\n**Key fixes:**\n1. **Empty-pool fallback:** When all candidates fail embedding threshold, return the best positional candidate (hard filters passed, so it's structurally sound)\n2. **Pre-threshold bilingual detection:** Before computing threshold, identify mixed-case title at position 0 followed by ALL_CAPS translation/romanization at position ≤ 2. Suppress the ALL_CAPS from threshold computation so its bonuses don't inflate the bar beyond the mixed-case title's reach.\n\n**Result:** 7/8 passing\n\n---\n\n### **Iteration 9 Final (Semantic Similarity for Bilingual Detection)**\n**Last issue:** Bilingual detection was count-based (`preAllCaps.length === 1`) but real recipes have multiple ALL_CAPS lines (section headers, serving sizes). \n\n**Fix:** Replace count-based guard with:\n- Positional check: ALL_CAPS candidate must be at position ≤ 2 (immediately after mixed-case title)\n- Semantic check: Candidate embedding similarity to position-0 title > 0.4 (ensures translation detection, not random ALL_CAPS)\n- Reuses already-computed embeddings (zero new calls)\n\n---\n\n## **Recurring Patterns Across All 9 Iterations**\n\n1. **Dedup \"shorter wins\" is backwards for multi-line titles** — persisted from iterations 1–6 until properly inverted\n2. **Structural bonuses inflate threshold, excluding valid candidates** — appeared in iterations 2–9\n3. **Embedding scoring penalizes ingredient-rich titles** — only addressed in iteration 9 with fallback\n4. **ALL_CAPS bias overwhelms position signal for bilingual recipes** — addressed iteratively, finally fixed by pre-threshold suppression with semantic validation (iteration 9)\n5. **Continuation joins fragile due to long dependency chain** — solved definitively in iteration 8 by pre-merging at input stage\n6. **Position-0 signal underweighted** — various attempts to boost it; solved in iteration 8 by making it a pipeline decision, not a bonus modifier\n\n**Core lesson:** Structural signals (position, continuation chars, ALL_CAPS in recipe context) were repeatedly being overridden by embedding scores. The shift toward treating structure as a pipeline shaper (pre-merge, pre-threshold suppression) rather than a bonus modifier finally made progress."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a7a3848af7fead06d (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 127597\ntool_uses: 18\nduration_ms: 31188</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f1cce918-fde6-46b5-9093-50476190ee9c","uuid":"40a00f29-2aa4-4dad-913c-1ffb771060db","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read all feedback.md and improvement-plan.md files in /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/ subdirectories (1 through 9). Give me a concise summary of each iteration: what failures were identified, what changes were proposed/made, and what patterns keep recurring. Focus on understanding what approaches have already been tried so we don't repeat them.\n\nRead thoroughly - check directories 1-404c596, 2-072e8fb, 3-a5a0dca, 4-4ecc581, 5-218113e, 6-8a6c985, 7-9a83c46, 8-b5177f1, 9-52aa0c8.","agentId":"a7a3848af7fead06d","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary of Title Extraction Iterations 1–9\n\nI've read all feedback and improvement plan documents. Here's a concise synthesis organized by iteration:\n\n---\n\n### **Iteration 1 (Baseline Failure Analysis)**\n**Failures identified:** 5 cases failed, 1 passed\n- **ARAYES SHRAK:** Short split titles lost to substring fragments\n- **Baked Eggs:** Metadata lines (SERVES) incorrectly joined with title\n- **Finnish Flatbreads:** OCR corruption fragments ranked higher than real titles\n- **Pizza Dough:** Embedding failed to rank technique-oriented titles correctly\n- **Saffron Wheat Buns:** Deep-document titles buried by early garbled text\n\n**Key patterns identified:**\n1. No recipe metadata filtering\n2. No OCR quality validation\n3. Embedding scoring unreliable for distinguishing titles from body text\n4. Position underweighted as signal\n5. Multi-line title joining fragile (no distinction between complete title and noise)\n6. `+`-join output format ambiguous (conflates multi-part titles with spurious matches)\n\n---\n\n### **Iteration 2 (Strategy: Bonuses)**\n**Plan:** Add position bonus, metadata blocklist, OCR quality gate, ALL_CAPS bonus, stricter thresholds\n**Problems:** Not fully implemented\n\n---\n\n### **Iteration 3 (Strategy: Invert Dedup, Reduce Position, Structural Heading)**\n**Key changes:**\n- Inverted substring dedup (longer candidate wins on ties)\n- Reduced position bonus from additive to multiplicative (tiebreaker only)\n- Added \"first structural ALL_CAPS heading\" bonus (+0.10)\n- Strengthened garble detection\n\n**Result:** Still failing — dedup logic backward\n\n---\n\n### **Iteration 4 (Diagnosis: Dedup + Threshold Leakage)**\n**Identified:** \n- Dedup \"shorter wins\" destroys correct multi-line joins (partial title beats full join)\n- Position boost inflates threshold, excluding late-document titles\n- Continuation logic depends on selecting correct base heading\n\n**Plan:** Use final score in dedup, make baseHeading embedding-aware, reduce threshold leakage\n**Problem:** Changes not implemented in code\n\n---\n\n### **Iteration 5 (Partial Implementation)**\n**Attempted:** Origin tracking, continuation join protection\n**Failures:** 3 cases still failing\n- Dedup still kills continuation joins (suffix fragments survive, kill complete join)\n- Structural bonus inflates threshold, excluding second recipe titles\n- OCR fragments hijack structural heading role\n\n---\n\n### **Iteration 6 (Embedding-Quality BaseHeading Selection)**\n**Key changes:**\n- Track candidate `origin` (single/2-line/3-line)\n- Protect continuation