g\n\n---\n\n### **Iteration 9 Final (Semantic Similarity for Bilingual Detection)**\n**Last issue:** Bilingual detection was count-based (`preAllCaps.length === 1`) but real recipes have multiple ALL_CAPS lines (section headers, serving sizes). \n\n**Fix:** Replace count-based guard with:\n- Positional check: ALL_CAPS candidate must be at position ≤ 2 (immediately after mixed-case title)\n- Semantic check: Candidate embedding similarity to position-0 title > 0.4 (ensures translation detection, not random ALL_CAPS)\n- Reuses already-computed embeddings (zero new calls)\n\n---\n\n## **Recurring Patterns Across All 9 Iterations**\n\n1. **Dedup \"shorter wins\" is backwards for multi-line titles** — persisted from iterations 1–6 until properly inverted\n2. **Structural bonuses inflate threshold, excluding valid candidates** — appeared in iterations 2–9\n3. **Embedding scoring penalizes ingredient-rich titles** — only addressed in iteration 9 with fallback\n4. **ALL_CAPS bias overwhelms position signal for bilingual recipes** — addressed iteratively, finally fixed by pre-threshold suppression with semantic validation (iteration 9)\n5. **Continuation joins fragile due to long dependency chain** — solved definitively in iteration 8 by pre-merging at input stage\n6. **Position-0 signal underweighted** — various attempts to boost it; solved in iteration 8 by making it a pipeline decision, not a bonus modifier\n\n**Core lesson:** Structural signals (position, continuation chars, ALL_CAPS in recipe context) were repeatedly being overridden by embedding scores. The shift toward treating structure as a pipeline shaper (pre-merge, pre-threshold suppression) rather than a bonus modifier finally made progress."}],"totalDurationMs":31188,"totalTokens":127597,"totalToolUseCount":18,"usage":{"input_tokens":4214,"cache_creation_input_tokens":63379,"cache_read_input_tokens":58434,"output_tokens":1570,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"stan